# Defensive default for a credential-handling tool: ignore EVERYTHING, then
# explicitly allow only the files that are safe to publish. This way any
# secret-bearing file — cert.conf, servers.txt, .ssh_passwords, rollback.txt,
# ad-hoc server lists, trace logs, the certs/ and logs/ dirs — is excluded by
# default and cannot be committed by accident. New files are ignored until you
# deliberately allow them here.
*

# --- Safe to publish -------------------------------------------------------
!.gitignore
!.gitattributes
!*.sh
!README.md
!LICENSE
!CONTRIBUTING.md
!CHANGELOG.md

# Templates only — these contain placeholders, never real secrets
!cert.conf.example
!servers.example.txt

# Tests and CI (un-ignore the dirs first, then their files)
!tests/
!tests/*.sh
!.github/
!.github/workflows/
!.github/workflows/*.yml

# Everything else (cert.conf, servers.txt, .ssh_passwords, rollback.txt,
# certs/, logs/, trace.txt, *.key, *.pem, *.csr, *.p12, *.pfx, ...) stays local.
